It sounds like you need a [PNCounter][1] from Akka&#39;s Distributed Data library. It uses Gossip to communicate the counter&#39;s state to the network. You also have fine grained control over read and write consistency. So, for example, you can do a `ReadMajority` where &quot;the value will be read and merged from a majority of replicas&quot;.

Incidentally, the PNCounter works as you describe, using two distributed counters to maintain increments and decrements.

  [1]: https://doc.akka.io/docs/akka/2.5.9/distributed-data.html?language=java#counters &quot;PNCounter&quot;

